to the editor even a dermatologist can influence nutrition schools cut down on fat and sweets in menus news article june 25 while in college i persuaded the administration to fill one compartment of a vending machine with apples instead of candy bars the apples sold out then while president of the brooklyn dermatologic society i asked that a tray of vegetables and low fat yogurt dip be added to the usual pastry tray at our meetings would these doctors bite they did the vegetables were eaten and most of the pastries were left behind stephen danziger md brooklyn june 25 2003

